default The Children’s Commissioner’s remit includes all children under 18 in England and young adults aged 18-20 who are care leavers or have a learning disability. 
defaultShe also has a duty to speak on behalf of all children in the UK on non-devolved issues which inc
defaultlude immigration, for the whole of the UK, and youth justice, for England and Wales. 
